25.title: "data-trk" Show Event Listener
25.notes:
The 'data-trk' attribute can be added to any HTML element.  It should have two parts (the event_category and the event_label), separated by a pipe character ("|").  
--
For example, to track a CTA button in the newsletter registation modal, just add the 'data-trk' element to have this listener fire utag.link events when it's displayed:
--
<div class="mail-cta" data-trk="modal|google-user-newsletter-registration" onclick="utag.extn.customModals.newsletterRegistration()"></div>
